Let's break down all individual expenses first before adding them up together:

Base Price of Truck: $30,000;
King Cab Upgrade Cost: An additional $7,500;  
Cost of Leather Seats: Given as one-third of the King Cab which equates to \($7,500\times \frac{1}{3}\) i.e., \$2,500;   
Running Boards Cost: They are said to cost $500 less compared to the leather seats meaning $(-\$2,500+\$500)$ or $-(\$2,500 -\$500)=-$2,000 since negative value doesn't make sense here we correct it to $2,500 – $500=$2,000;    
Upgraded Exterior Light Package: This adds another $1500 to our calculation.      
Now add these amounts :     
Total Expense Calculation would look like this ->         
Start Off With Base Price       
Then Add Each Feature Individually        
Final Total = Initial amount + Added Ext
